md:
giải nghĩa từ "attended" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.

* attended (verb) /əˈtɛndɪd/
	+ Meaning: to be present at an event or a meeting; to go to a place or an event
	+ Vietnamese: tham dự, tham gia, có mặt tại
	+ Example sentence: She attended the conference in New York last week.
	+ Related words: attend, attendance, attending

* attended (verb) /əˈtɛndɪd/
	+ Meaning: to take care of someone or something; to look after
	+ Vietnamese: chăm sóc, theo dõi, quan tâm
	+ Example sentence: The nurse attended to the patient's wound.
	+ Related words: attend, attention, attentive

* attended (adjective) /əˈtɛndɪd/
	+ Meaning: having been present at an event or a meeting
	+ Vietnamese: đã tham dự, đã tham gia
	+ Example sentence: The attended guests were given a special gift.
	+ Related words: attend, attendance, attending
